						               													<description>Break-A-Leg is a pick and pass card drafting game for 2-5 players that plays in about 30 minutes. Players take on the role of a theatrical producer hiring the best cast, creative, and crew, while simultaneously foiling the plans of the opposing producers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During each of three recruitment sessions (rounds), players collect cards representing team members from the four theatrical production team areas: Actors, Designers, Run Crew, and Front of House.  Players draft additional Directors, Specialists, and Apprentices to augment their production.The ensemble is assembled into teams, then scored, and players are given a representative for each team they have formed. Bonuses reward multi-round planning, and on the fly strategy adjustment.  At the end of the game, &amp;ldquo;Ghost Light&amp;rdquo; cards collected throughout the rounds score bonuses, and players are rewarded if they have earned a representative from all four teams.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Break-A-Leg is a lightweight game that is easy to learn, yet offers a plethora of options for experienced players, such as draft signaling, counter-picking, multi-round planning, and draft-pick priority.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
